{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VokAmCTjqKHET6hgvfy3SE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All pods are ready and the replica set is healthy: **1 PRIMARY** (`mongodb-replica-1`) and **2 SECONDARYs** (`mongodb-replica-0`, `mongodb-replica-2`).\n\n**Root cause:** The `health-overrides` ConfigMap contained a stale entry `mongodb-replica-1: legacyHealthPass123`. The health-check script checks this ConfigMap for per-pod password overrides before falling back to the shared secret — so `mongodb-replica-1` was authenticating with the wrong password, causing the readiness probe to fail with `Authentication failed`.\n\n**Fix:** Removed the stale `mongodb-replica-1` key from the `health-overrides` ConfigMap. Once Kubernetes refreshed the mounted volume (~30s), the pod's health-check started using the correct password from the shared secret (`healthpass123`) and the readiness probe began succeeding."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":280,"cache_read_input_tokens":36752,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":280},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e8fffc05-70e9-462e-9e53-97b6eb4f3e2b","uuid":"613a7671-4270-4b2f-b2f3-6649fa7e05ce","request_id":"req_011Cc5LJrMnNrs6JsyEUD9NA"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":263706,"duration_api_ms":76360,"ttft_ms":2686,"ttft_stream_ms":1897,"time_to_request_ms":32,"num_turns":18,"result":"All pods are ready and the replica set is healthy: **1 PRIMARY** (`mongodb-replica-1`) and **2 SECONDARYs** (`mongodb-replica-0`, `mongodb-replica-2`).\n\n**Root cause:** The `health-overrides` ConfigMap contained a stale entry `mongodb-replica-1: legacyHealthPass123`. The health-check script checks this ConfigMap for per-pod password overrides before falling back to the shared secret — so `mongodb-replica-1` was authenticating with the wrong password, causing the readiness probe to fail with `Authentication failed`.\n\n**Fix:** Removed the stale `mongodb-replica-1` key from the `health-overrides` ConfigMap. Once Kubernetes refreshed the mounted volume (~30s), the pod's health-check started using the correct password from the shared secret (`healthpass123`) and the readiness probe began succeeding.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"e8fffc05-70e9-462e-9e53-97b6eb4f3e2b","total_cost_usd":0.2926037000000001,"usage":{"input_tokens":14,"cache_creation_input_tokens":20362,"cache_read_input_tokens":382859,"output_tokens":3653,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":20362,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":208,"cache_read_input_tokens":36752,"cache_creation_input_tokens":280,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":280},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":647,"outputTokens":18,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.000737,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":14,"outputTokens":3653,"cacheReadInputTokens":3